@aliveli186 what version of truffle are you using? This should have been resolved in [v5.3.10](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/releases/tag/v5.3.10) 😅 . If you're on a previous version you can upgrade with the following command `npm uninstall -g truffle && npm install -g truffle`

> What could be the problem and how can I compile with "-s ASSERTIONS=1" to get more information?

That output shouldn't be displayed but you can examine the end of the dump, which may have information on the rejected promise or error that caused the issue.
